== Charts ==

Upon the release of ''Overexposed'', due to strength of digital downloads, "Wipe Your Eyes" debuted at number 80 on the US ''Billboard'' Hot 100 for the issue dated July 14, 2012.<ref name="us debut"/> After the release of the album, as a results of the downloads the song debuted on the South Korea [[Gaon Chart|Gaon International Chart]] at number 18 on June 24, 2012, with sales of 25,772 digital copies.<ref name="South Korea"/> The next week, it fell to number 23 and sold additional 11,876 copies.<ref name="South Korea1">{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/online/download/list.gaon?nationGbn=E|title=South Korea Gaon International Chart (Week, July 1, 2012 to July 7, 2012)|publisher=Gaon Chart|accessdate=January 31, 2013|language=Korean}}</ref> It stayed on the chart for total of four weeks.<ref name="South Korea2">{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/online/download/list.gaon?nationGbn=E|title=South Korea Gaon International Chart (Week, July 22, 2012 to July 28, 2012)|publisher=Gaon Chart|accessdate=January 31, 2013|language=Korean}}</ref>

